Privacy Policy for RPT Trainer
Effective Date: June 11, 2026
Introduction
Welcome to RPT Trainer ("we," "our," or "us"). We respect your privacy and are committed to protecting your personal information. This Privacy Policy explains how the RPT Trainer mobile application (the "App") handles your information.
Please read this Privacy Policy carefully. By using the App, you agree to the terms of this Privacy Policy. If you do not agree with the terms of this Privacy Policy, please do not access or use the App.
Information We Collect
We do not collect any information. The App has no accounts, no analytics, no crash reporting, and makes no network calls. All information you input into the App, including:

Workout data
Exercise records
Weight and repetition information
User preferences and settings

is stored locally on your device and is never transmitted to us or to any third party.
Data Storage and Security
All your workout data is stored locally on your device. We do not operate servers and we never receive your workout information. This means:

Your workout data remains on your device even when offline
Your data is protected by your device's built-in security features
You maintain complete control over your data

Data Export
The App can export your training history as a CSV file. An export happens only when you trigger it, and the resulting file is shared only through the iOS share sheet to a destination you choose. The App itself never sends this file anywhere.
Third-Party Services
The App does not integrate with any third-party services, SDKs, or analytics providers, and it does not connect to Apple Health.
Your Choices
You can delete all app data at any time by:

Deleting the app from your device
Using the "Reset All Settings" option in the app settings to restore preferences to their defaults
Manually clearing app data through your device settings

Children's Privacy
Our App is not directed to children under the age of 13. Because the App collects no information at all, it does not knowingly collect personally identifiable information from children under 13.
Changes to This Privacy Policy
We may update our Privacy Policy from time to time. We will notify you of any changes by posting the new Privacy Policy on this page and updating the "Effective Date" at the top of this Privacy Policy. You are advised to review this Privacy Policy periodically for any changes.
